comment:
* A list of packages and associated attribution tags that supports easy membership checks. Supports
 * "wildcard" attribution tags (ie, matching any attribution tag under a package) in additional to
 * standard checks.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: mPackageTags
variables.comment: an empty set value matches any attribution tag (ie, wildcard)

methods.name: public boolean isEmpty()
methods.comment: * Returns true if this instance is empty;

methods.name: public boolean includes(@NonNull String packageName)
methods.comment:
* Returns true if the given package is found within this instance. If this returns true this
     * does not imply anything about whether any given attribution tag under the given package name
     * is present.

methods.name: public boolean includesTag(@NonNull String attributionTag)
methods.comment:
* Returns true if the given attribution tag is found within this instance under any package.
     * Only returns true if the attribution tag literal is found, not if any package contains the
     * set of all attribution tags.
     *
     * @hide

methods.name: public boolean containsAll(@NonNull String packageName)
methods.comment:
* Returns true if all attribution tags under the given package are contained within this
     * instance.

methods.name: public boolean contains(@NonNull String packageName, @Nullable String attributionTag)
methods.comment: * Returns true if the given package and attribution tag are contained within this instance.

methods.comment: * Returns true if the given PackageTagsList is a subset of this instance.
